  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study was conducted to demonstrate post-abdominoplasty analgesic duration consequent to
      three different surgically infiltrated LA techniques; bilateral TAPB, bilateral RSB and
      subcutaneous infiltration using the same volume of 0.25% bupivacaine (40 ml). Pain score,
      total analgesic rescue requests and the total amount of systemic rescue analgesia used in the
      first postoperative day in addition to any detected postoperative complications were also
      recorded.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
